'''Quentor''' was the false alias, given by [[Fligh]] to [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], for a thief by the name of [[Aarno Dering]], who operated in stolen goods and information for profit.

It was also the name of a yellow-tailed summerbird pet of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate.]]

==Biography==
On the planet [[Euceron]], the thief "Quentor" approached a shady information dealer by the name of [[Fligh]] during the [[Galactic Games/Legends|Galactic Games]] of [[26 BBY/Legends|26 BBY]]. Fligh learned that [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]] would win the "fixed" swoop obstacle course event, and in turn shared that information with [[Didi Oddo]], who then told it to [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]].

[[Jocasta Nu/Legends|Jocasta Nu]], at Kenobi's request, did a search of the name in the [[Jedi Archives/Legends|Jedi Archives]] and discovered that "Quentor" was a yellow-tailed summer bird. The unofficial pet of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]], Quentor lived in the eaves of the building and the [[Senator/Legends|Senators]] provided him with fruit and crumbs to eat. [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] knew, then, that [[Fligh]] had lied to him about his source. Kenobi tracked down Fligh anew to inquire again about his true source, only to discover that Fligh had been protecting Aarno Dering.

